BERLIN , December 17 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The German government will provide Cuba next year with 3 million marks as the start sum of its first official development aid to Cuba , the Ministry of Development Aid said Friday in Berlin .
This adjustment of the policy toward Cuba has shown that Germany `` is on the same line with its partners in the European Union , '' said Development Aid Minister Heidemaria Wieczorek - Zeul .
Germany 's goal is to `` promote Cuba 's change toward democracy , '' she said , adding that the sum would also support the opposite groups in Cuba .
The German government promised to help Cuba fight against desertification and drought .
The project may last 10 to 12 years and Germany 's total contribution is expected to reach 11 million marks , the minister said .
